Police say a fire which almost completely destroyed a barn was started deliberately.
The incident took place at a farm off Taunton Road in Wiveliscombe, Somerset, between 00:00 and 00:15 GMT on 17 March, Avon and Somerset Police said.
The damage to the barn and its contents is estimated to be about Â£100,000, according to the force.
Officers are appealing for anybody who may have information about the incident to contact them.
